{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddc6b9efa-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"§ 1.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Time for election of Senators","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"At the regular election held in any State next preceding the expiration of the term for which any Senator was elected to represent such State in Congress, at which election a Representative to Congress is regularly by law to be chosen, a United States Senator from said State shall be elected by the people thereof for the term commencing on the 3d day of January next thereafter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddc6e0ffb-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1914-06-04/ch103/s1"},"text":"June 4, 1914, ch. 103, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/38/384"},"text":"38 Stat. 384","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1934-06-05/ch390/s3"},"text":"June 5, 1934, ch. 390, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/48/879"},"text":"48 Stat. 879","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddc6e0ffc-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddc6e0ffd-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"iddc6e0ffe-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1934—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1934-06-05"},"text":"June 5, 1934","children":[],"tail":", substituted “3d day of January” for “fourth day of March”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"iddc6e0fff-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Constitutional Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The first section of Amendment XX to the Constitution provides in part: “* * * the terms of Senators and Representatives [shall end] at noon on the 3d day of January, of the years in which such terms would have ended if this article had not been ratified; and the terms of their successors shall then begin.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Time for election of Senators, see Const. Art. I, § 4, cl. 1.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Vacancies in the Senate, see Const. Amend. XVII.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
